Algorithm for Merge Sorted Array using auxiliary array:
Create a new array arr of size m + n.
Use three pointers:
i = 0   // pointer for nums1
j = 0   // pointer for nums2
k = 0   // pointer for arr
Compare values from both arrays while both pointers are valid:
while i < m and j < n
If nums1[i] is smaller or equal, put it into arr[k] and move i.
Otherwise, put nums2[j] into arr[k] and move j.
After placing one value into arr, always move k.
If any elements are left in nums1, copy them into arr.
If any elements are left in nums2, copy them into arr.
Finally, copy all elements from arr back into nums1.

class Solution {
    public void merge(int[] nums1, int m, int[] nums2, int n) {
        
        int len = m + n;
        int[] arr = new int[len];

        int i = 0;
        int j = 0;
        int k = 0;

        while (i < m && j < n) {
            if (nums1[i] <= nums2[j]) {
                arr[k] = nums1[i];
                i++;
            } else {
                arr[k] = nums2[j];
                j++;
            }

            k++;
        }

        while (i < m) {
            arr[k] = nums1[i];
            i++;
            k++;
        }

        while (j < n) {
            arr[k] = nums2[j];
            j++;
            k++;
        }

        for (int x = 0; x < m + n; x++) {
            nums1[x] = arr[x];
        }
    }
}


Create a new array of size m + n. 
Use two pointers to compare values from nums1 and nums2. Add the smaller value into the new array. 
After one array finishes, copy the remaining values. Finally, copy the result back into nums1.

class Solution {
    public void merge(int[] nums1, int m, int[] nums2, int n) {
        int[] result = new int[m + n];

        int i = 0; // pointer for nums1
        int j = 0; // pointer for nums2
        int k = 0; // pointer for result

        while (i < m && j < n) {
            if (nums1[i] <= nums2[j]) {
                result[k] = nums1[i];
                i++;
            } else {
                result[k] = nums2[j];
                j++;
            }
            k++;
        }

        while (i < m) {
            result[k] = nums1[i];
            i++;
            k++;
        }

        while (j < n) {
            result[k] = nums2[j];
            j++;
            k++;
        }

        for (int x = 0; x < m + n; x++) {
            nums1[x] = result[x];
        }
    }
}
